          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-By authors. A nondestructive method for carbon",
                "determination in layers of 3-10-mum thickness is",
                "considered. The method is based on using the C-12(d,n)",
                "nuclear reaction with simultaneous account of surface",
                "contamination by means of the C-12(d,p)C-13 competitive",
                "reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The thin target containing 15-mug/cm**2 of carbon was",
                "used. The thin target was made by means of C-12 ion",
                "implantation into high purity molybdenum backing."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "1. Spectrum of prompt particles of nuclear reactions",
                "measured after the annealing.",
                "2.  Relative backscattering yield of N-13 recoil nuclei",
                "as a function of the atomic number of target.",
                "3. Metrological parameters of proposed method."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
